content.description: Up the left side of the rock.  Good sidepulls out left, use the little ledges for feet.
content.protection: Rack of quickdraws is sufficient.  There are bolts all the way to the top where there is a 2-BA.
content.location: Follow the directions to Yardsale then find route #1 on the beta photo.  Rap off or walk off.

content.description: Fun slab climbing up the middle of the rock.
content.protection: Rack of quickdraws is sufficient.  There are bolts all the way to the top where there is a 2-BA.
content.location: Follow the directions to Yardsale then find route #2 on the beta photo.  Rap off or walk off.

content.description: The chimney to the right of the crag which starts after some steep dirt and plant scrambling
content.protection: You might get a big cam in there, but it is fun to just solo, its pretty mellow and short
content.location: The prominent chimney (Can be seen in the upper right corner of the topo picture)

content.description: Get on up to the little roof which is the crux.
content.protection: Quickdraws or other anchor setup for the top where there is a 2-BA.
content.location: Follow the directions to Yardsale then find route #6 on the beta photo.  Rap off or walk off.

content.description: Good sidepulls out to the right.  Crux is at the bulge about halfway up.
content.protection: Rack of quickdraws is sufficient.  There are bolts all the way to the top where there is a 2-BA.
content.location: Follow the directions to Yardsale then find route #3 on the beta photo.  Rap off or walk off.
